    "industrial_process_notes": "Developed in 1928 in several laboratories, including Otto Röhm's; commercialized in 1933 under the trademark Plexiglas by Röhm & Haas, with Perspex and Lucite following shortly after from other manufacturers. Produced via free-radical polymerization: emulsion, solution, or bulk processes. Cast acrylic sheet has better thermal stability, higher solvent-craze resistance, and a wider thermoforming range than extruded sheet.",
